@NODE  "Description" "Object: Universe"

@{b}@{u}OBJECT@{uu}@{ub}
Name:    Universe
Version: 1
ID:      ID_UNIVERSE
Module:  @{"Kernel" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Functions"}
Include: @{"system/misc.h" LINK "GMSDev:Includes/system/misc.h/Main"}
Type:    Simple

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
The universe object was introduced to support the CopyStructure() function.
It  is  used as center point for data storage, carrying common named fields
such as Width, Height, etc.

Use of the Universe object in your own programs may be limiting, as it does
not actually "do" anything, except to provide a way of sharing information.

@{b}@{u}ACTIONS@{ub}@{uu}
The Universe object supports the following actions:

     @{"Free()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Free()"} - Free the Universe object.
     @{"Get()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Get()"}  - Get a new Universe structure.
     @{"Init()" LINK "GMSDev:AutoDocs/Kernel.guide/Init()"} - Initialise a Universe object.

@{b}@{u}STRUCTURE@{uu}@{ub}
The Universe structure consists of the following public fields:

  AmtColours
  BmpType
  ByteWidth
  Channel
  Height
  InsideHeight
  InsideWidth
  InsideXOffset
  InsideYOffset
  Frequency
  Length
  Octave
  Palette
  Planes
  Priority
  Raster
  ScrMode
  XOffset
  YOffset
  Source
  Task
  Volume
  Width

@EndNode
